step('225', 15, 'while the onions cook, prepare the vegetables.'). 
step('225', 16, 'use a box grater to grate the courgette into a bowl.'). 
step('225', 17, 'add a pinch of salt, mix and set aside.'). 
step('225', 18, 'slice the bottom off the baby gem lettuce and separate the leaves into a large mixing bowl.'). 
step('225', 19, 'slice the artichokes into quarters and add to the bowl along with the baby gem.'). 
step('225', 20, 'open up the pitta breads so you have two thin layers of bread, then tear them into roughly 2-inch squares (they dont have to be neat).'). 
step('225', 21, 'put a frying pan over a medium heat, add your butter and a tbsp of olive oil.'). 
step('225', 22, 'once hot, add the pitta bread and fry until golden and crunchy.'). 
step('225', 23, 'take off the heat and add a pinch of salt, a tsp of chilli flakes and a tsp of sumac and toss well.'). 
step('225', 24, 'set aside to cool.'). 
step('225', 25, 'pop the pan back over a medium-high heat and add a splash of olive oil.'). 
step('225', 26, 'give the grated courgette a squeeze, then add them to the pan.'). 
step('225', 27, 'move it around and let it fry for 3 or 4 mins.'). 
step('225', 28, 'set aside to cool, then repeat with the peas.'). 
step('225', 29, 'to assemble, mix the now-cooled onions and their cooking oil into the labneh.'). 
step('225', 30, 'add the peas and courgettes to the bowl with the baby gem and artichokes, a pinch of salt, the juice of 1 lemon.'). 
step('225', 31, 'add the labneh and mix well to coat everything.'). 
step('225', 32, 'just before youre ready to serve, mix through the pitta (keep a few to sprinkle on top).'). 
step('225', 33, 'finish with lots of chopped mint, plenty of sumac and olive oil.'). 
step('225', 34, 'serve and enjoy!.'). 
