step('248', 7, 'remove the pork belly slices from the fridge and place into a baking tray with a drizzle of vegetable oil.'). 
step('248', 8, 'cover the tray tightly with tin foil.'). 
step('248', 9, 'cook for 1 1/2 hours, flipping the slices over half way through.'). 
step('248', 10, 'we want them to be cooked through and soft, but not falling apart.'). 
step('248', 11, 'whilst your pork cooks, make your spicy apple glaze.'). 
step('248', 12, 'wrap your two cooking apples in tin foil and place them at the bottom of the oven, or into the coals of a barbecue.'). 
step('248', 13, 'cook until the apples are super soft - about 20 mins.'). 
step('248', 14, 'set the apples aside until cool enough to handle.'). 
step('248', 15, 'remove the core and seeds as best you can and place the flesh in a food processor.'). 
step('248', 16, 'add a tablespoon of honey and your bulls-eye carolina reaper extra hot sauce.'). 
step('248', 17, 'add more or less to taste.'). 
step('248', 18, 'blend the mixture, and add the juice of your lemon.'). 
step('248', 19, 'set aside.'). 
step('248', 20, 'mix your mayo.'). 
step('248', 21, 'add your mayonnaise to a bowl, then grate in your clove of garlic and squeeze in your lemon juice.'). 
step('248', 22, 'mix thoroughly.'). 
step('248', 23, 'pour your vinegar and sugar into a pan along with 690ml of water.'). 
step('248', 24, 'bring to a boil.'). 
step('248', 25, 'once the sugar has dissolved, leave to cool.'). 
step('248', 26, 'shred your cabbage, onion and carrot very finely.'). 
step('248', 27, 'you can use a mandoline or a very sharp knife.'). 
step('248', 28, 'finely chop your parsley.'). 
step('248', 29, 'combine your sliced cabbage, onion and carrot in bowl and mix in your parsley.'). 
step('248', 30, 'dress with vinegar up to an hour before serving.'). 
step('248', 31, 'remove your tray from the oven and place your pork belly slices onto a plate to cool slightly.'). 
step('248', 32, 'heat your barbecue to a high heat.'). 
step('248', 33, 'in a small bowl, combine the cooking juices from the pork and 1/3 of your spicy apple glaze.'). 
step('248', 34, 'place your pork belly slices onto the barbecue and brush on your glaze.'). 
step('248', 35, 'flip the pork belly slices, then continue to glaze until youre happy with the colour and coverage.'). 
