step('543', 3, 'break the chocolate into a bowl, add the butter.'). 
step('543', 4, 'melt in the microwave in 30 second bursts, or over a saucepan of simmering water (making sure the bottom of the bowl doesnt touch the water).'). 
step('543', 5, 'once melted stir through the coffee, and set aside.'). 
step('543', 6, 'next separate the egg whites and yolks between two large bowls.'). 
step('543', 7, 'using an electric whisk, whisk the egg whites until they hold their shape, looking like little soft mountains in the bowl.'). 
step('543', 8, 'tip the sugar into the bowl with the egg yolks.'). 
step('543', 9, 'without cleaning the beaters (theres no need) whisk the egg yolks and sugar together until they are super pale, thick and voluminous.'). 
step('543', 10, 'be patient, you want the egg yolks and sugar to treble in size - it will take a good 5 minutes.'). 
step('543', 11, 'sift the cocoa powder into the whisked egg yolks, add a big pinch of sea salt and scrape in the melted chocolate mixture.'). 
step('543', 12, 'stir together using a large metal spoon or spatula then gently fold in a third of the egg whites to loosen the cake batter, then fold in the rest.'). 
step('543', 13, 'the tip here is to be confident in your folding - you want to keep as much air as possible in the cake so make decisive large turns with your spoon.'). 
