time('650', 250). 
servings('650', 12). 
cuisine('650', 'american'). 
step('650', 1, 'warm the milk, butter and sea salt in a small saucepan over a low heat, stirring constantly, until the butter has melted.'). 
step('650', 2, 'remove from the heat and allow to cool until lukewarm.'). 
step('650', 3, 'combine the flours, sugar, yeast, cinnamon and cardamom in a large bowl (a stand mixer bowl if you have one).'). 
step('650', 4, 'make a well in the mixture then add the eggs (beaten) and pour the pumpkin puree into the centre.'). 
step('650', 5, 'pour the lukewarm milk mixture into the bowl, then knead using the stand mixer fitted with the dough hook attachment for 8 minutes.'). 
step('650', 6, 'alternatively, if you want to get a bit messy, stir everything until it comes together, then knead on a lightly oiled surface until the dough becomes less sticky and elastic.'). 
step('650', 7, 'shape the dough into a ball and put it into a lightly oiled bowl.'). 
step('650', 8, 'cover with a clean tea towel or some oiled clingfilm and leave to prove at room temperature for 2 hours until the dough has doubled in size.'). 
step('650', 9, 'to make that classic cinnamon filling, mix the butter and brown sugar in a bowl with the nutmeg, half of the ground cinnamon and all the ground cloves until it forms a smooth paste.'). 
step('650', 10, 'set aside, with the remaining cinnamon in a separate bowl.'). 
step('650', 11, 'for the sticky glaze, pour the malted drink into a saucepan and simmer over a medium heat for about 20 minutes until it has reduced to 50 ml.'). 
