step('734', 10, 'make sure each piece is completely covered.'). 
step('734', 11, 'transfer to the tray.'). 
step('734', 12, 'fill up the biggest, deep, heavy-bottomed saucepan you have half way with oil.'). 
step('734', 13, 'put on a medium heat to maintain a steady temperature and heat until simmering.'). 
step('734', 14, 'to test that the oil is ready, mix 1 tsp of the leftover buttermilk with the flour to make a craggy dough.'). 
step('734', 15, 'drop it into the oil and you are looking for it to brown, puff up and rise to the surface in a minute - any quicker and the oil is too hot.'). 
step('734', 16, 'starting with a tester, fry the chicken in batches for around 12 minutes until super crispy - turn once halfway.'). 
step('734', 17, 'check the first one to make sure the chicken is cooked through.'). 
step('734', 18, 'if the chicken browns too quickly on the outside but isnt cooked all the way through, you will need to turn the temperature down on the oil.'). 
step('734', 19, 'if you have a thermometer you want it to be 160c/ 320f.'). 
step('734', 20, 'the temperature will drop once the cold chicken goes in so keep adjusting the heat.'). 
step('734', 21, 'dont cook more than 3 pieces at once.'). 
step('734', 22, 'transfer the fried chicken to a wire rack over a tray lined with kitchen roll.'). 
